      name: "Vancomycin",
      type: "Glycopeptide antibiotic",
      action: "Inhibits bacterial cell wall synthesis by binding to D-ala-D-ala terminus of peptidoglycan precursors; bactericidal against gram-positive organisms including MRSA",
      sideEffects: "Red man syndrome (histamine-mediated flushing with rapid infusion), nephrotoxicity, ototoxicity, thrombocytopenia",
      contra: "Known hypersensitivity; use with caution in renal impairment (dose adjust based on trough levels and AUC monitoring)",
      pearl: "Infuse over at least 60 minutes to prevent red man syndrome; target AUC/MIC 400-600 for serious MRSA infections; monitor trough levels and renal function; commonly paired with piperacillin-tazobactam for empiric sepsis coverage"
