        correct: 1,
        rationale: "Absolute risk communication (10 out of 100 reduced to 5 out of 100, NNT = 20) provides honest, transparent information that patients can meaningfully weigh against side effects and costs. Relative risk (50% reduction) inflates perceived benefit and can mislead patients. Appeals to guidelines or what others choose undermine individual autonomy and shared decision-making."
